Convert a Dimension Field Type to Measure

When you load data into a dataset, CRM Analytics tags a measure field as a dimension if it contains unexpected strings or characters. To use measure functionality, such as calculating the average, use the To Measure transformation to change the dimension field type to measure.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To create a recipe: Edit Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes

During the column type conversion, the Dimension to Measure transformation rounds decimals to the nearest whole number. For example, 300.2939 becomes 300.

On the column header of the dimension field, click , and then select To Measure.
Click Add and save the recipe.

Run the recipe to create a new field with the measure field type.
title: Converting Dimension Fields to Measures in CRM Analytics
